window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>This audiobook is filled with magical and adventurous guided imagery for children around the world. In today’s overly stimulated society, meditation is a useful technique for reducing stress and anxiety, whilst increasing self-esteem, creativity, focus, and joy.</p> <p>Please note: This audiobook is written in rhyme, and designed to be listened to by a resting child.</p> <p>Designed as a playful adventure, your child can enjoy being taken on this fun meditation. They will be both guided with the visual meditation and encouraged to use their imagination to explore the secret magical world, allowing them to disconnect from the stress of the day, wind down, and relax.</p> <p>The chapters include adventuring the various worlds under their bed, including:</p> <p>Chapter 1 - The Gold Door</p> <p>Chapter 2 - The Farm Door</p> <p>Chapter 3 – The Jelly Door</p> <p>Chapter 4 - The Cloud Door</p> <p>Chapter 5 - The Chocolate Door</p> <p>Chapter 6 - The Rainbow Door</p> <p>Chapter 7 - The Train Door</p> <p>Chapter 8 - The Under the Sea Door</p> <p>Chapter 9 - The Fairy Door</p> <p>Chapter 10 - The Blue Door</p> <p>Chapter 11 - The Dinosaur Door</p> <p>Chapter 12 - The Tall Door</p> <p>Chapter 13 - The Make Your Own World Door</p> <p>Created by positive psychology author Amba Brown.</p> <p>About the author:</p> <p>Amba Brown is an Australian author, living in New York City who has written multiple non-fiction books published by various houses including HarperCollins Publishers and John Catt Educational Publishing. She is also the creator of the Finding Your Path Book series.</p> <p>Amba has been featured internationally, sharing her message with the <i>Huffington Post</i>, <i>Reader’s Digest</i>, and at TEDx.</p> <p>Amba holds a degree majoring in psychology and sociology, with a psychological science honors specializing in positive psychology.&nbsp;</p> <p>She is also a member of the International Positive Psychology Association and is passionate about alleviating the anxieties of youth. Her goal is to share these tools as far and wide as possible. For more information, visit findingyourpathbooks.com.</p>"; 
